			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Reconstructed OoW Songlist<a name="70749"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 8 04 2:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Examining this list, I can tell you right now, that with instrument mods (AAs, Instruments, clickies) some of these songs would be godlike. I'm sure some bards would get over 200 hp per tick with those regen songs.
<br />

<br />
Did you look at the upgrades other classes got?
<br />

<br />
I mean some of that stuff looks really nice, but consider balance as an issue.
<br />

<br />
Snare would have been too powerful for single pulling creatures that are normally nearly impossible to single pull. The mez just makes chanters look even worse. A bard can mez adds while running them to the group. A chanter just gets raped if they gain aggro on mezzing (Yeah I know they have runes, but that won't help at all in some zones).
<br />

<br />
You listed a lot of songs that we didn't really need an upgrade for. Psalm of Veeshan is already very powerful, same with Harmony of Sound (Yelhun's Mystic Silence would be insane with instrument mods added on, and Silence seems too powerful).
<br />

<br />
Also did we really need more haste? Currently as is with our songs, people with 40 percent or greater haste items won't get anymore benefit. No reason to increase haste on our songs more (Item Haste + Spell/Song Haste Cannot exceed 100%; Then Add Overhaste/&quot;version 3 haste&quot;).
<br />

<br />
I think only shamans should get spells which increase the stat cap, as they're supposed to be the best stat buffers in the game. Did you see how it was for them before OoW Released?
<br />

<br />
Well those are just some of my thoughts. I'm sure others may think about it differently.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
