			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Reconstructed OoW Songlist<a name="70752"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 8 04 5:16 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Examining this list, I can tell you right now, that with instrument mods (AAs, Instruments, clickies) some of these songs would be godlike. I'm sure some bards would get over 200 hp per tick with those regen songs.
<br />

<br />
Did you look at the upgrades other classes got? </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
These same bards would be in groups where 200hp a tick would be
<br />
the bare minimum for them to even have a chance to notice that
<br />
the song is playing.  Do you know how much the Heal over Time
<br />
spells do now a days on a crit?  The Highest mod is 4.2 and I
<br />
did consider it when picking my numbers.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I mean some of that stuff looks really nice, but consider balance as an issue. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Thank you, and yes I do believe other classes would also need
<br />
to get some upgrades. 
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Snare would have been too powerful for single pulling creatures that are normally nearly impossible to single pull. The mez just makes chanters look even worse. A bard can mez adds while running them to the group. A chanter just gets raped if they gain aggro on mezzing (Yeah I know they have runes, but that won't help at all in some zones). </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Ok, I agree with snare as I put it up there would be open to
<br />
abuse.  Perhaps instead of modeling it after RoTime I should 
<br />
focus on AAssonance, the dot component should reduce pulling
<br />
abuses, but we would still benefit from not having to snare over
<br />
and over and over.  
<br />

<br />
I disagree with your mez comment tho.  I believe chanters have
<br />
a big edge on crowd control and bards need help.  If I have the
<br />
option of mezz'ing adds while running them to the group I'll 
<br />
choose to single pull instead.  I'm talking about using mez when
<br />
there are no other options, and in OoW getting a mez resist on
<br />
a seemingly trash mob that it should land on often means the
<br />
death of a groupmember.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">You listed a lot of songs that we didn't really need an upgrade for. Psalm of Veeshan is already very powerful, same with Harmony of Sound (Yelhun's Mystic Silence would be insane with instrument mods added on, and Silence seems too powerful).
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Psalm of Veeshan is very powerful yes.  It's a group song.  The
<br />
one I listed is an AE song.  We haven't had an upgrade to AE
<br />
resist songs since forever.  The new AE song would not stack
<br />
with veeshan.  It would also block guardian rythmns.  It would
<br />
increase the resist stat cap by as much resists as its pumping
<br />
so that even people who already are capped on resists will see
<br />
a difference.  It would stack with the old AE songs so that
<br />
people who aren't near the caps for resists would see a huge
<br />
bonus from a bard playing these songs.  It's the same relative
<br />
bonus people used to see when bards played the AE resist songs
<br />
when they first came out, and I'd like that limelight
<br />
back.
<br />

<br />
Harmony of Sound is useless as a 3 tick song.  The upgrade I
<br />
proposed would validate bards as a debuffer on raids, as well
<br />
as facilitate the job of slowing mobs in groups when no other
<br />
slower present.  Snare as well.
<br />

<br />
Silence, although powerful, is something I always fancied bards
<br />
getting.  The limit to being cast on mezzable mobs only balances
<br />
it well in conjunction with the 2 minute recast.  3 Ticks is
<br />
really not all that long, and I'm sure some people would find it
<br />
weak!
<br />

<br />
 <blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Also did we really need more haste? Currently as is with our songs, people with 40 percent or greater haste items won't get anymore benefit. No reason to increase haste on our songs more (Item Haste + Spell/Song Haste Cannot exceed 100%; Then Add Overhaste/&quot;version 3 haste&quot;).</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
A lot of people never actually got the 40 percent or greater 
<br />
haste items, and are stuck/satisfied with 34/36 percent worn
<br />
haste.  This is why the best chanter haste is 66 percent, as far
<br />
as I know.  
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I think only shamans should get spells which increase the stat cap, as they're supposed to be the best stat buffers in the game. Did you see how it was for them before OoW Released? </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This part has me a bit confused.  If I understand this correctly,
<br />
you believe that overhaste (a stat that goes passed the cap)
<br />
is not something bards should have?
<br />

<br />
Bards are the original cap busters, and in a cap busting, chance
<br />
to crit increasing expansion not only should we have songs of
<br />
that type but we should be dominating the field!
<br />

<br />
I really appreciate you taking the time to respond to my crazy
<br />
post, and I already changed the snare on my list.  Will post a 
<br />
revised list if for some reason people feel nice enough to
<br />
comment on it as well <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
thanks much!
<br />

<br />
'Stuce</span></td>
