				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">first, many things you asked for, it's not that they could not be done, but it would take signifigant coding changes for it to be done. I'm mainly talking about the instrument modifiers you asked. right now instrument mods only effect hard stats. things like +str, +resists, +regen. Asking for an instrument to effect the resist modifier is most definatly possible, but IMO unneccessary coding. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
That is a very good point, I mistakenly confused the earlier mez
<br />
songs with resist adjustment (Dreams of Anyonae) with the one
<br />
that had a debuff component (Sionache's Dreams, Pixie Strike).
<br />
In a revised list I would go with a static -10 resist check, and 
<br />
a magic debuff component that would facilitate keeping the mob
<br />
mezzed once it initially lands, like we used to be able to. (As an
<br />
aside, I also just found out that chanters get a new focus that
<br />
decreases all aggro they gain from any entrall spell, so bards are
<br />
in dire need of help in the CC department).
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">We should have definatly recieved an AE chromatic resist song. It should not stack, otherwise it would have to be too weak to be usefull.
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
If the new AE chromatic resist song raises caps as well as the
<br />
stats, it does not have to be weak to be useful while being
<br />
allowed to stack with the other two AE songs.  It will be over
<br />
written by PoVeeshan, and it will block Guardian Rythmns.  In
<br />
my mind it is the direct upgrade to guardian rythmns, there is
<br />
no reason we should be playing a lvl 18 song at raids.  Perhaps
<br />
it could be tweaked a little, by keeping the MR the same but
<br />
lowering the FR/CR/PR/DR by 15 or so.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">We should have recieved the duration snare and resist debuff songs we've been asking for all this time. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I completely agree with you.  I also believe that by keeping a
<br />
DoT component on the snare, you can prevent a lot of pulling
<br />
abuses that bards would do with a duration snare, which seems
<br />
to be the overwhelming cause of the ninja nerf right before OoW
<br />
went live.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">We should have recieved a melee/spell rune song that is both twistable and worth using.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I completely agree.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Our 3 garbage rizlona upgrades (OOPS 1 is a downgrade, 1 is identical) should have had added effects like healing focus or improved criticals. (mages and wizards dont even need the dmg focus anymore, they have self focus that is as good or better). </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I completely agree.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">adding more utility songs like the 3 tick silence would be awesome. I was so excited about the 9th spell slot, but unfortunatly we didn't recieve any songs worthwhile for that slot. I kid you not, a good amount of the time that slot is empty or unused. my default raid/group spell set has the 5 minute recast BBB nuke stored there for the OMG 1800 bard crit hotkey.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I feel the exact same way.  I am sick and tired of playing 
<br />
Haste v1, Haste v3, Veeshan, and marr.  It's been these songs
<br />
for way too long.  Variety is the spice of life!
<br />

<br />
Thanks very much for your comments, I will revise the 
<br />
mesmerize song to reduce unnecessary coding problems.
<br />

<br />
'Stuce</span></td>
